<HEADLINE>
<P>
AIR BAG THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * We have read with great interest "Air Bag Theft an Expanding New Problem," 
April 7. An excellent report, finely written and serving the public good.We 
salute you for delving into this growing problem. 
</P>
<P>
 However, we were taken aback by one paragraph, which states, in part, "auto 
dismantlers buy the bags as salvage items with no questions asked." This would 
seem to imply that all or any auto dismantlers are involved in such unsavory 
conduct, which, of course, is not true. 
</P>
<P>
 We are professional, licensed, regulated and a highly policed industry -- the 
nation's 16th largest. We deal in salvaged vehicles, usually obtained from 
insurance auctions and sales. Rather than collaborate with thieves, as the 
article might imply, we work with various law enforcement agencies to rid our 
industry of just the people the article describes. In fact, most of the 
criminal activity investigated by the various agencies is reported by our own 
members. 
</P>
<P>
 We hope any future articles of this nature will make it crystal-clear that you 
are talking about a minute number who would violate the law. 
</P>
<P>
 TERRY FISKIN, Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
 Auto Dismantlers Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 of Southern California 
</P>
</TEXT>
