<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHOOSING A NEW JUSTICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In choosing a Supreme Court justice, an excellent legal mind, by itself, is 
not a sufficient criterion.There are many cold-blooded, excellent legal minds. 
Another criterion, such as life experience, which contributes to how a person's 
point of view is formed and how he will make decisions, is an equally valuable 
resource. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional factors, such as a commitment to balance on the court, should be 
weighed. With these considerations in mind, how about giving Professor Anita 
Hill the nod on this one? 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD F. DOWLING 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Niguel 
</P>
