<P>
NEWS BITES : WHAT'S A GOOD SPINACH WINE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fetzer Vineyards announces a recipe contest ("The Great Salad Toss") for 
"wine-friendly" salad recipes. This is more of a challenge than you might 
think; most connoisseurs insist vinegar spoils the flavor of wine.The deadline 
is June 15; 15 finalists and their guests will get to spend a September weekend 
at the Fetzer Food & Wine Center, where the winner of the $5,000 grand prize 
will be announced. Call (800) 959-4035 for contest guidelines. Write 100 Times: 
Nothing in Excess 
</P>
<P>
 A recent issue of the journal Pediatrics reported on eight children, aged 14 
to 27 months, whose abnormally slow growth was traced to drinking too much 
apple juice. When their parents started providing three full meals and two or 
three snacks a day -- and keeping the apple juice ration below half a cup -- 
the children started to grow normally again. Wholesome though it is, apple 
juice just doesn't provide enough protein, minerals and fat for growing 
children. Wheat Thins Aren't Thin? We're Shocked, Shocked! 
</P>
<P>
 Nabisco Biscuit Co. says it will introduce reduced-fat Oreos -- as well as 
low-fat Ritz Crackers and Chips Ahoy! and reduced-fat Triscuits, Better 
Cheddars and Wheat Thins -- on April 25. The original varieties will continue 
to be available. Maybe It's Ultra-Lean 
</P>
<P>
 It must have sounded like a hip name at some brain-storming session in 
Budapest. A firm selling a new premium line of Hungarian pork decided to call 
itself Hungapig. 
