<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BREAD PUDDING NOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ABBY MANDEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When making bread pudding, it pays to toss bread cubes with the liquid and 
other ingredients in a mixing bowl, so that everything can be well mixed. For 
best results, the bread must absorb all the liquid as evenly as possible before 
being transferred to the baking dish. Some breads do this more quickly than 
others. ABBY MANDEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar; Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042194-0029 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 034118 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
