<HEADLINE>
<P>
RODNEY TROVINGER; VIDEO EXECUTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rodney William Trovinger, vice president and chief financial officer of LIVE 
Entertainment Inc. and LIVE Home Video, has died. He was 43. 
</P>
<P>
 Trovinger died Sunday of AIDS at a hospital in Arlington Heights, Ill., the 
Hollywood company announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The certified public accountant previously worked as vice president for 
finance at the Mantle White Co. and as senior manager of the accounting firm 
Fox and Co. Both firms are in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Born in Lodi, Calif., Trovinger studied accounting and music at the University 
of the Pacific in Stockton. 
</P>
<P>
 He is survived by his companion, Robert Moon; his parents, Evelyn and John 
Trovinger, and two brothers, Douglas and Mark. 
</P>
<P>
 The family has asked that any memorial donations be made to the AIDS Legal 
Council of Chicago, 220 S. State St., Suite 1330, Chicago, Ill. 60604. 
</P>
