<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MISCELLANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southwest Conference athletic directors have scheduled an April 29 meeting in 
Dallas to "discuss how we're going to close down the conference," Texas A&M 
athletic director Wally Groff said. It appears Rice, Texas Christian and 
Southern Methodist are heading to the Western Athletic Conference.Their move 
comes after Texas, Texas A&M, Baylor and Texas Tech left the SWC for the Big 
Eight. The latest moves will leave Houston as the lone SWC school. 
</P>
<P>
 Prize money for the U.S. Open tennis championships will be increased to a 
record $9,360,100 for this year's tournament, which begins Aug. 29. The singles 
title for both men and women will be worth $550,000, an increase of $15,000 
from last year. Doubles winners will earn $200,000 per team with mixed doubles 
first prize set at $46,500. Names In The News 
</P>
<P>
 Karl Benson was named as replacement for Joe Kearney as commissioner of the 
Western Athletic Conference. Benson, the Mid-American Conference Commissioner, 
will take over June 30 for Kearney, who is scheduled to retire after 14 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
