<P>
CUBAN OFFICIALS DENY REPORTS CASTRO IS AILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cuban Foreign Ministry sources Wednesday denied reports in some foreign media 
that President Fidel Castro had suffered a health problem such as a heart 
attack or brain hemorrhage. 
</P>
<P>
 "He enjoys excellent health," the sources said, adding that Castro, 67, is 
likely to be present at a special session of Parliament on May 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
