<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; PANEL APPROVES EAST SIDE DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Camarillo Planning Commission has approved a developer's request to build 
160 condominiums and 42 single-family houses on a 19-acre parcel on the city's 
east side. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission voted unanimously Tuesday night to approve the project by the 
Camarillo-based Pardee Construction Co.The plan must still go before the City 
Council.  
</P>
<P>
 The parcel is near the intersection of Mission Oaks Boulevard and Woodcreek 
Road. The development is less dense than was stipulated in the developer's 
original 1991 application, project manager Bill Teller said. He added that the 
company opted to go with a lighter-density development because of the 
surrounding neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert W. Burrow, a senior planner with the city, said the commission asked 
the developer to erect a wall along Mission Boulevard and change driveway 
entrances on the thoroughfare to dampen the level of traffic noise that could 
affect residents of the project. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission also required that at least 20% of the units be made available 
to low-income families. The City Council is scheduled to consider the project 
at its May 11 meeting. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
