<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; DRIVER CHARGED IN PEDESTRIAN'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County prosecutors have charged a Simi Valley man, who is accused of 
running over a 54-year-old man, with vehicular manslaughter while intoxicated 
and evading arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Rodriguez, 39, is being held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of $10,000 
bail.He was charged Tuesday and is set to be arraigned April 28, said Deputy 
Public Defender William Markov. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez was arrested Friday after his car hit several parked cars and struck 
Raphael Lachmiller, who was walking from his car to his family's house on 
Whitcomb Avenue in Simi Valley, police said. Lachmiller died later from 
injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 An off-duty Los Angeles County sheriff's deputy in the area saw Rodriguez's 
vehicle strike two parked cars and followed him, police said. The deputy then 
saw Rodriguez's vehicle hit Lachmiller, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez's vehicle ran a stop light while police were chasing him, and his 
car finally stopped when he crashed into a planter, police said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
