<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE BASEBALL; SANTA MARGARITA RALLIES TO TIE TUSTIN FOR FIRST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FORREST LEE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Overlooked? Santa Margarita Coach Tip LeFebvre believes so. 
</P>
<P>
 A five-run rally in the sixth inning propelled host Santa Margarita to a 7-5 
Sea View League baseball victory over Tustin and into a first-place tie with 
the sixth-ranked Tillers. Both teams are 6-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Reightley's two-run double with two outs in the sixth drove in Paul 
Nicotra and pinch-runner Lou Manera for the winning run. Robbie Redwitz added 
an RBI single to cap the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin, ranked No. 2 in Division III with a 14-5 record, had entered the game 
as one of the county's hottest teams, winning 10 of its last 11 games and all 
six in league. Santa Margarita has been hot of late, too, LeFebvre said, but it 
hadn't attracted as much attention, particularly after a 1-6 start. 
</P>
<P>
 "Some people don't understand . . . we've played Brea-Olinda, Fountain Valley, 
Marina twice, Edison, San Clemente and Troy," said LeFebvre, whose team won its 
sixth in a row and improved to 10-7 overall. "We've played the top teams to be 
ready for this." 
</P>
<P>
 Looks were deceiving early against Tustin, too. Ryan Winmill's three-run homer 
to left off Ed Dryden in the first gave Tustin a 3-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles cut the gap to 3-2 with a run each in the first and second innings. 
Tustin increased it to 5-2 in the third on a sacrifice fly by Rick Gonzalez and 
Jeff Cunningham's run-scoring single. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicotra and Barry Hawkins each had RBI singles in the fifth, scoring Brian 
Griffin and Chris Collins to slice Tustin's lead to 5-4. Two batters later, 
Reightley, who was two for three with two doubles and two RBIs, doubled to 
left-center for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 4, Corona del Mar 2 (8 innings) -- Geoff Noisy's two-run single in the 
eighth gave Irvine (10-10, 3-4) the come-from-behind victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 7, Woodbridge 6 (9 innings) -- Eddie Mejia's leadoff ninth-inning 
home run gave Saddleback (10-8-1, 4-3) the victory. Mejia finished with three 
hits and two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 University 4, Newport Harbor 1 -- Tim Blackbrun pitched a two-hitter and 
struck out seven, as University (1-6 in league) won its first league game of 
the season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
