<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; GLENN HITS FOR CYCLE AS BUENA PARK POUNDS SUNNY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ryan Glenn hit for the cycle, leading Buena Park to a 14-5 victory over Sunny 
Hills in a Freeway League baseball game Wednesday at Sunny Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 After a single and a double in the early innings, Glenn hit a homer in the 
sixth and tripled in the seventh. Glenn, who hit his first two homers of the 
season Friday, finished with three runs batted in and two runs scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Timmy Jones also had four hits and scored three runs, stole two 
stolen bases and drove in a run for Buena Park (10-6, 6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Davis pitched a complete game, allowing nine hits and five runs. 
</P>
