<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: UC SANTA BARBARA LANDS DANNY PRINCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Danny Prince, who established school and Foothill Conference three-point 
scoring records at Antelope Valley College, has signed to play basketball at UC 
Santa Barbara, Antelope Valley Coach Newton Chelette said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Prince, a 6-foot-1 point guard from Quartz Hill High, set a school single-game 
record last season with 11 three-point baskets. He led the state with 178 
three-point baskets, also a Marauder single-season record. 
</P>
<P>
 He averaged 23.1 points during the regular season, and was the conference 
player of the year and an all-state selection. 
</P>
<P>
 Prince also considered Colorado State, San Diego State, Cal State Fullerton, 
Cal State Long Beach and UCLA. Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake High incorrectly announced last week that two of its 
volleyball players have made commitments to attend colleges. 
</P>
<P>
 Wolverine outside hitter Matt Sebree was reported to have committed to attend 
Colorado, but he said Tuesday night he has not committed, and is considering 
Colorado, California, UCLA and USC. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was talking to (Harvard-Westlake Athletic Director Gary) Thran about 
Colorado, and I guess he mistook it to mean that I was definitely going there," 
Sebree said. 
</P>
<P>
 Setter Court Young, reported to be headed for UCLA, is still also considering 
USC and Penn State. Cycling 
</P>
<P>
 Shaun Cronkhite of Chatsworth, a member of the Valley-based Nutra-Fig Cycling 
Team, won the 40-mile Carlsbad Criterium last Sunday in Carlsbad. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Thurlow Rogers of Van Nuys was sixth. The Nutra-Fig team won the 
overall team title. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday, Rogers placed fourth at the 40-mile San Diego Criterium to lead 
Nutra-Fig to the team title. Boxing 
</P>
<P>
 Nine members of the San Buenaventura Boxing Club will compete in the Junior 
Olympics May 13-15 at Santa Fe Springs. The boxers range in age from 8 to 16. 
</P>
<P>
 The club is accepting donations to help finance the trip. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (805) 648-1895. Football 
</P>
