<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS: WOOD RANCH BARBEQUE LOOKS FOR A LOCATION WHERE IT CAN LAUNCH ITS 
PLANNED EXPANSION. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wood Ranch Barbeque and Grill of Moorpark could be part of a chain restaurant 
in the very near future. At least that's what Eric Anders, the head of the 
establishment, is hoping for. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're looking frantically to find another location, somewhere between 
Calabasas and Oxnard," he said. "We're looking for a high-traffic area with 
excellent parking and a neighborhood that has some businesses, so we can draw a 
good lunch business as well as dinner." 
</P>
<P>
 Anders said the 2-year-old Barbeque and Grill was designed with the creation 
of a Southern California chain in mind. "We expect to open one or two a year," 
he said. "We draw so many people from Agoura to Ventura, it's what our 
customers are asking for." 
</P>
<P>
 The existing restaurant is located at 540 New Los Angeles Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Here's a slightly premature "Welcome Home" for Mabel Chase, co-owner of the 
City Bakery and Cafe in Ventura, who will be back in Ventura County within two 
weeks. Chase, her husband George Keenen (the other co-owner) and their son have 
spent the past year in England. Keenen is expected back in May. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 When Chase does get here, look for at least one change at City Bakery. 
</P>
<P>
 The restaurant has been serving dinners Wednesdays through Fridays since 
January. And now, said chef Reece Keck, the soon-to-return owner is looking to 
add Saturday nights to the lineup. "I could picture extending it even further 
this summer," Keck said. 
</P>
<P>
 Keck, the original chef at Ventura's Voila Cafe (now Cafe Zack) has prepared 
the dinner menus -- which change weekly -- since the restaurant began featuring 
them. Each week's fare includes one fish, one poultry, one meat, one pasta, one 
pizza and one vegetarian dish. 
</P>
<P>
 "I feel like that's going to meet everyone's requests," said Keck, "but it 
also gives me a lot to play with." Keck said she decides on specific menu items 
pretty much at the last moment. "It's just kind of whatever my mood is." 
</P>
<P>
 City Bakery is located at 2358-C Main St. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042194-0157 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 034246 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
April 21, 1994, Thursday, Ventura West Edition 
</P>
