<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROSTITUTION RAID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nearly two dozen people were arrested and charged with prostitution-related 
offenses during a raid on an acupuncture clinic in a strip mall in the City of 
Industry last week, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 After serving a search warrant last Thursday afternoon at Gale Acupuncture, an 
acupuncture and massage parlor at 15341 Gale Ave., deputies arrested a man and 
six women for maintaining and residing in a "house of ill fame," said Lt. David 
H. Kading of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department.Nearly 300 
bulk-packaged condoms were seized. 
</P>
<P>
 Kading said an eight-hour sting operation that followed the raid resulted in 
the arrest of 13 men for suspicion of soliciting prostitution from female 
undercover deputies. 
</P>
<P>
 The offenses are punishable by up to six months in jail or a fine not 
exceeding $1,000. 
</P>
