<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: POMONA; REGISTRAR COUNTING SOTO RECALL PETITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pomona City Councilwoman Nel Soto could face a recall election this year if 
the county registrar validates enough of the 1,648 signatures handed in to City 
Hall last week on recall petitions. 
</P>
<P>
 The Recall Soto Committee, led by teacher and community activist Bob Jackson, 
needs 1,440 valid signatures -- equal to 25% of the registered voters in Soto's 
District 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson, whom Soto defeated in the 1991 District 1 council race, alleges that 
Soto, through acceptance of campaign contributions, has sold out to special 
interests such as the billboard industry. Jackson and his group also allege 
that Soto has misappropriated some of her election campaign funds, using money 
to pay for work on her house. 
</P>
<P>
 Soto, who says she's done nothing illegal in spending or accepting campaign 
contributions, argues that Jackson is simply a sore loser who's trying to 
tarnish her reputation in an effort to get elected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
