VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: L. A. OFFERS GRANTS FOR ENVIRONMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By REBECCA BRYANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is offering grants to encourage Angelenos to improve and protect 
their environment. 
</P>
<P>
 A grant of $1,000 will be given out in each City Council district.The grants 
are sponsored by the Los Angeles Environmental Affairs Commission and Southern 
California Gas Co. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's both a reward and an incentive for people to do things in their 
community to promote environmental protection and environmental awareness," 
said Lillian Kawasaki, general manager of the Los Angeles Environmental Affairs 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Grants will go to schools, nonprofit groups or other organizations that apply 
with plans such as tree planning, community gardens and cleanups -- "anything 
that increases the urban quality of life," Kawasaki said. "We have so few 
really green and open spaces in the city we thought it would be a good focus 
for this year's grant." 
</P>
<P>
 The commission, the utility and community representatives will be judges. 
</P>
<P>
 Deadline for applications is June 30. 
</P>
