<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNCIL OKS 3RD OFFICE FOR ALARCON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council approved a request Wednesday by Councilman 
Richard Alarcon to open a third office in his east San Fernando Valley 
district, making him the only council member with more than two district 
offices. 
</P>
<P>
 Alarcon said the office at 81228 Sunland Blvd., Sun Valley, will be in a 
building he will share with the Sun Valley Chamber of Commerce and the Los 
Angeles Police Department.It will be open by next month. 
</P>
<P>
 He defended his proposal for a third office, saying his district is elongated 
and lacks representation in the southeast end of the district. Alarcon operates 
district offices in Sylmar and Pacoima. 
</P>
<P>
 Alarcon said the costs of running an additional office will not force him to 
exceed his office budget because he shares leasing costs for his Sylmar office 
with Councilman Hal Bernson and shares costs for his Pacoima office with 
Pacoima Enterprise Zone officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
