<HEADLINE>
<P>
VANDALS DEFACE MURAL AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mural at a Northridge elementary school that pictured youths of various 
races and ethnic groups has been defaced by vandals who marred it with racial 
and religious epithets, Los Angeles police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The vandalism at Castlebay Lane Elementary School, 190120 Castlebay Lane, 
apparently occurred Tuesday night or early Wednesday morning, police 
said.School officials said the graffiti markings were erased before most 
students saw them. 
</P>
<P>
 "We take this problem very seriously," Principal Natalie Messenger said. "I 
have the sense that it might have been older kids because it was relatively 
high up on the walls and all the words were spelled correctly." 
</P>
<P>
 Messenger said teachers at the school, where the student enrollment is about 
one-half Anglo and one-third Asian American, will discuss the graffiti with 
students today. TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
