<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; $2.5-MILLION GYM GETS COUNCIL'S OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council on Tuesday unanimously approved a $2.5-million gymnasium to 
be built at Hurless Barton Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The 23,000-square-foot gym, which will be the second in the city, is planned 
for the south side of the park next to Yorba Linda Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials hope to reach a joint-use agreement with Placentia-Yorba Linda 
Unified School District that would give the school use of the facility during 
school hours on weekdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Adult and youth sports teams and other city-sponsored recreational activities 
would have priority after school and on weekends. 
</P>
<P>
 In return, the school district would be responsible for about 30% of the cost 
of maintaining the facility, which is expected to be about $120,000 annually. 
</P>
<P>
 The gym has been a project of Councilman John M. Gullixson since he took 
office in 1990. Gullixson, who is active in a youth basketball league, has 
frequently complained about the lack of indoor facilities for basketball 
players. 
</P>
<P>
 He often refers to the disparity between the city's 58,000 residents having 
one gym at Travis Ranch Activity Center, and Placentia's 40,000 residents 
having five gyms. 
</P>
<P>
 "Travis Ranch is a tremendous facility, but it gets a lot of use," Gullixson 
said.DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
