<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; MARCH TO RAISE FUNDS FOR 'HEALTHIER 
BABIES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 5,000 people are expected at a march here Saturday to raise money 
for the March of Dimes. The nonprofit organization raises about a third of its 
national budget at the yearly marches, which will be held in more than 1,400 
communities, organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County organizers hope to raise more than $425,000 to prevent birth 
defects. The event is titled "Walk for Healthier Babies." 
</P>
<P>
 Money raised will be used for research, community service advocacy and health 
education. The March of Dimes is now working to reduce infant mortality and low 
birth weight. 
</P>
<P>
 Marchers will meet at the Magnolia Street entrance to Huntington State Beach 
on Pacific Coast Highway and follow an eight-mile, oceanfront route. To 
participate, call (714) 631-8700. WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
