<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Telephone & Telegraph Co. said it earned $1.09 billion in the first 
three months of the year as its revenue rose 5%. 
</P>
<P>
 The telecommunications and computer conglomerate said the revenue growth 
reflected a modest increase from long-distance telephone service as well as 
double-digit percentage gains from sales of equipment and financial services. 
</P>
<P>
 AT&T's profit amounted to 80 cents a share for the three months ended March 31 
and contrasted with a loss a year earlier of $6.83 billion, or $5.07 a share, 
when its results were reduced by huge onetime charges. 
</P>
<P>
 Without the charge a year ago, its latest profit was up 17% from income of 
$936 million, or 69 cents a share, in the first quarter of 1993. Revenue for 
the quarter rose to $16.56 billion from $15.72 billion a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
