<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Allstate Raises Quake Estimate to $950 Million: The insurer said its estimate 
of Northridge earthquake insurance claims is now $950 million instead of $600 
million, citing hidden damage from the Jan. 17 quake and aftershocks.Allstate 
predicted higher costs per claim, "resulting primarily from engineering reports 
which revealed previously unreported hidden damage to dwellings." The company 
expects about 40,000 claims. Other large insurers have also raised their 
estimates. The industry's official estimate for total insured damage is $4.5 
billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
