<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD BEA MAXWELL: ST. VINCENT GALA KEEPS MEALS READY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BEA MAXWELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Vincent's Meals-on-Wheels raised $15,000 at an April 11 benefit gala 
hosted by Cuisine a Roulettes with Karim and Sharif Souki, owners of the Monkey 
Bar. Cuisine a Roulettes is the support group for the St. Vincent program that 
prepares and delivers meals to some 2,000 homebound people. The event was 
chaired by Katherine Kilroy and Irene Weingarten. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Venice Family Clinic is grateful for the latest contribution from Frederick R. 
Weisman, a new Lexus that was auctioned with proceeds used to match an earlier 
$100,000 contribution. Ticket sales totaled $95,000 for expanded health 
services to those in need. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gay and Lesbian Alliance Against Defamation/Los Angeles raised $150,000 at its 
annual GLAAD/LA Media Awards on March 19 at the Century Plaza. Honorees 
included Aaron Spelling, Harvey Fierstein and Roberta Achtenberg. Robin 
Williams, Lily Tomlin, Matthew Modine, Heather Locklear, Amanda Bearse and 
Mariel Hemingway were among the guests. Co-hosts were Stockard Channing and 
Bruce Davison. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Travelers Aid Society of Los Angeles received $12,000 at a luncheon and bridge 
party April 7 at the Wilshire Country Club. The benefit was hosted by the 
Irving Walker Auxiliary of the society. In addition to helping travelers in 
distress, Travelers Aid maintains the Teen Canteen in Hollywood, where homeless 
teen-agers receive food, shelter and counseling. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 American Red Cross/Earthquake Relief Fund received $30,000 from the cast of 
"Sunset Boulevard." The money was raised over the past several weeks through 
sales of autographed posters signed by Glenn Close and other members of the 
cast. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Regional Food Bank received 492 pounds of food from the Snyder 
Chiropractic Health Center in West Los Angeles. The center held its fifth 
annual Hope Day event March 22, offering free consultations, examinations and 
X-rays in exchange for non-perishable food. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Serra Project, established to provide assistance to people with HIV and 
AIDS, raised $60,000 at its recent "A Faire of the Heart" at Pacific Design 
Center. In addition, two checks totaling $80,000 were presented to Serra 
president Sister Jane Francis Power by the Sisters of St. Joseph of Orange and 
St. Joseph Health System. The gift to was a tribute to honor her achievements 
and her 80th birthday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Commission on Assaults Against Women received $10,000 for 
earthquake relief and disaster counseling from the California Community 
Foundation, the United Way of Los Angeles and Los Angeles Women's Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
