<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: CLEAN SHAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 So what's it like to shave your legs? -- if you're a boy, that is. 
</P>
<P>
 The Accolade, the student newspaper at Sunny Hills High School in Fullerton, 
went right to the source -- males on the swim team -- for the answer. 
</P>
<P>
 Many male swimmers are at first repelled by the idea of shaving their arms and 
legs to improve their swimming times, especially since some haven't even 
started shaving their faces yet. 
</P>
<P>
 "It really hurt. It stung and burned so bad . . . some of my skin was taken 
off," said one male swimmer. Reported another: "The first time you get in the 
water, it feels really strange. You get fast and slimy. The worst part is when 
it is growing back and itches." 
</P>
<P>
 The up side? Girls "really admire how soft our legs are." One female 
concurred: "I think it's kind of funny . . . when their legs look better than 
yours." 
</P>
</TEXT>
