<HEADLINE>
<P>
'MACBETH' TO OPEN ART'S 8TH SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN HERMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shakespeare's "Macbeth" will launch the Alternative Repertory Theatre's 
1994-95 season in September, the company announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The upcoming season, ART's eighth, will also include Arthur Miller's "Death of 
a Salesman" and Paul Zindel's "The Effects of Gamma Rays on Man-in-the-Moon 
Marigolds," as well as staged readings of Truman Capote's "A Christmas Memory" 
and a work to be named. 
</P>
<P>
 ART, which operates in a 61-seat storefront venue, has 431 subscribers. That 
is more than triple the number it started out with, spokesman Gary Christensen 
said, but also represents a decline from its record of 500 last season. 
</P>
<P>
 To encourage new subscriptions, he noted, ART is launching a "pay as you go" 
plan that will enable playgoers to become season ticket holders for $25 instead 
of $70, the full subscription price to all five shows. A "pay-as-you-go" 
subscriber will be charged $7 at the door for each production attended, in 
addition to the initial fee. 
</P>
<P>
 "We hope this will be especially attractive to seniors and students and 
anybody who lives on a budget," Christensen said. Single tickets for 
non-subscribers will remain $16. The '94-95 Season: 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 29-Nov. 12: "Macbeth," by William Shakespeare. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 9-24: Staged reading of "A Christmas Memory," by Truman Capote. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 20-March 4: "Death of a Salesman," by Arthur Miller. 
</P>
<P>
 * March 30-April 21: To be named (possibly a one-woman black musical or a 
Latino work with performances in English and Spanish). 
</P>
<P>
 * May 12-June 24, 1995: "The Effect of Gamma Rays on Man-in-the-Moon 
Marigolds," by Paul Zindel. 
</P>
<P>
 All productions will be at Alternative Repertory Theatre, 1636 S. Grand Ave., 
Santa Ana. Information: (714) 836-7929. 
</P>
