<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: AVALON; CITY COUNCIL SELECTS INTERIM MEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An interim City Council member has been appointed to fill the seat vacated 
when Ralph J. Morrow Jr. was elected mayor last week, but Avalon voters will 
return to the polls in the fall to fill the seat permanently. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Nelson, 40, who came in third in a race for two City Council seats, will 
fill the position until the Nov. 8 statewide election, when voters will elect a 
council member to serve the remaining two years of Morrow's four-year term. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson, a businessman, was selected unanimously after the new council was 
seated Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "(The council) did a lot of research around town and the majority of opinion 
was (to) just appoint the third-highest vote-getter," City Clerk Shirley Davy 
said. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
